						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Śivāṅkurēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This incomplete record engraved in Grantha characters gives a number of birudas including <hi rend="italic">Ayyaṅgamalaparāyara Gaṇḍagaṇḍagōpāla-śirah-kantu[for ndu]ka-krīḍāvinōda Pāṇḍya-sthāpanāchārya</hi>, apparently of a Hoysala king. Palaographically it may be assigned to the 13-14th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
